==Chinese==
===[[Hokkien]]===
===Etymology===
One word from [[Singlish]]. Not easily comprehended by foreigners in Singapore. Given meaning is afraid to die. Just used to describe people who are gutless. Usually only used by Singaporeans. Nevertheless its origin is from a Chinese dialect. Done in a humourous way of course. A fictious character from a Singapore drama called Mr Kiasu. Also the cousin of Mr Kiasu.
===Noun===
# {{pejorative}} a [[coward]]


'''Kiasi'''

# (colloquial) (derogatory) a coward
#:Why are you so Kiasi? You won't die from getting a small cut on the finger.

# (colloquial) (derogatory) a nickname
#:He is such a Kiasi, he does not have the guts to take a chance at anything.

